    <data key="d0">Vodafone NZ: Data Driven Omni Channel Contact Center via Automation and Continuous Improvement</data>
    <data key="d1">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OQKOHNtyz3E</data>
    <data key="d2">Vodafone New Zealand migrated their legacy on-prem contact center solution to AWS to address high complexity (81,000 interaction pathways), high cost, and lack of visibility. The new architecture leverages AWS Connect as the core, with Amazon Lex for intent simplification (down to 200 intents). A universal, modular contact flow system is enabled by Lambda and DynamoDB for dynamic configuration. The solution supports over 2,500 agents and handles over 1 million phone calls per month. A robust CI/CD pipeline using AWS DevTools and Terraform enables infrastructure as code for automated deployments. All contact data, including Contact Lens outputs, is ingested into Snowflake for analytics via dashboards, providing a continuous feedback loop for agents, team leads, and developers to improve customer experience.</data>
    <data key="d3">interactive, data_ingestion, control</data>
    <data key="d4">True</data>
  </graph>
